# FL-DCD-7224-4 Digital Light Source Controller
# STM32CubeMX Configuration for STM32G030C8T6
#
# NOTE: This is a text description of the CubeMX configuration.
#       To generate the actual .ioc file, use STM32CubeMX GUI or
#       use the STM32CubeIDE project provided separately.
#
# =====================================================================
#  System Configuration
# =====================================================================
#
# MCU: STM32G030C8Tx
# Package: LQFP48
# Clock: HSI 16MHz → PLL × 4 → 64 MHz SYSCLK
# Flash: 0 wait states (64MHz is borderline, 1 WS may be needed)
#   → Actually STM32G030 needs 1 WS at 64MHz, configured as FLASH_LATENCY_2
#     for extra safety margin
#
# =====================================================================
#  Pin Assignments (matching schematic)
# =====================================================================
#
# PA0  - ADC1_IN0     (Over-current sense, analog)
# PA4  - GPIO_INPUT   (TRIG1, trigger input)
# PA5  - GPIO_INPUT   (TRIG2)
# PA6  - GPIO_INPUT   (TRIG3)
# PA7  - GPIO_INPUT   (TRIG4)
# PA8  - TIM1_CH1     (PWM1 output, AF2)
# PA9  - USART1_TX    (RS232 TX, AF1)
# PA10 - USART1_RX    (RS232 RX, AF1)
#
# PB3  - TIM1_CH2     (PWM2 output, AF1)
# PB4  - TIM1_CH3     (PWM3 output, AF1)
# PB5  - TIM1_CH4     (PWM4 output, AF1)
# PB6  - GPIO_INPUT   (KEY_L, Button CH, pull-up)
# PB7  - GPIO_INPUT   (KEY_M, Button -, pull-up)
# PB8  - GPIO_INPUT   (KEY_R, Button +, pull-up)
# PB10 - GPIO_OUTPUT  (CH455G SCL, bit-bang)
# PB11 - GPIO_OD      (CH455G SDA, bit-bang, open-drain)
# PB12 - GPIO_OUTPUT  (LED_B, Power indicator)
# PB13 - GPIO_OUTPUT  (LED_S, Mode1 indicator)
# PB14 - GPIO_OUTPUT  (LED_P, Mode2 indicator)
#
# =====================================================================
#  Peripheral Configuration
# =====================================================================
#
# TIM1 (Advanced Timer):
#   - Clock source: Internal (64 MHz APB1 × 1 timer multiplier)
#   - Prescaler: 0
#   - Counter period: 999 (for 64kHz) / 255 (250kHz) / 127 (500kHz)
#   - Mode: PWM Generation CH1-CH4
#   - Polarity: High
#   - Auto-reload preload: Enable
#
# USART1:
#   - Mode: Asynchronous
#   - Baud rate: 115200
#   - Word length: 8 bits
#   - Stop bits: 1
#   - Parity: None
#   - NVIC: USART1 global interrupt (priority 1)
#
# ADC1:
#   - IN0 (PA0)
#   - 12-bit resolution
#   - Software trigger
#   - Sampling time: 39.5 cycles
#
# =====================================================================
#  Build Instructions
# =====================================================================
#
# Option 1: STM32CubeIDE
#   - Import this project
#   - Build with "Release" configuration
#   - Flash via ST-Link
#
# Option 2: Makefile + arm-none-eabi-gcc
#   - Install ARM toolchain
#   - Place STM32CubeG0 HAL library in Drivers/
#   - Run: make
#   - Flash: openocd -f interface/stlink.cfg -f target/stm32g0x.cfg \
#            -c "program build/fl-dcd-7224.elf verify reset exit"
#
# Option 3: PlatformIO
#   - Create STM32G030C8 project
#   - Copy Core/ files into src/
#   - pio run -t upload
